This is the Military Forces of New South Wales Memorial which 

&quot;Buried here are Lieut. T. Hammond, Lieut. R. Bedford, Corpl. J. McKee and Bugler C. Bennett, killed in April 1891 by the premature explosion of a submarine mine during the Middle Head Easter encampment.&quot;

